	<p>This credit applies only for tuition and fees at accredited colleges that are approved by the Department of Education.  In other words, if the school offers FFELP loans, it is an accredited college approved by the Department of Education.  Cost of books, supplies, and equipment may be included only if they must be paid to the school in order to enroll.</p>
	<p>Room and board, transportation, and living expenses may not be included in the credit you claim.  If a student receives a scholarship for full tuition, this credit cannot be used.</p>
	<p>A family can claim a total Lifetime Learning Tax Credit of $2000 per year.  In technical terms, the Lifetime Learning Tax Credit is available for 20% of the first $10,000 of qualified educational expense.  An advantage of this credit over the Hope Scholarship Tax Credit is that there is no limit on the number of years that the Lifetime Learning Tax Credit can be used.</p>
